Real DOM
updates slow.
DOM manipulation is very expensive.


Virtual  DOM-> updates faster.
Can’t directly update HTML
Updates the JSX if element updates.
DOM manipulation is very easy.
No memory wastage.


What is React?
front-end JavaScript library developed by Facebook in 2011.
 follows the component based approach which helps in building reusable UI components.
used for developing complex and interactive web and mobile UI.



 features of React? 

uses the virtual DOM instead of the real DOM.
It uses server-side rendering.
It follows uni-directional data flow or data binding.



JSX?
JavaScript along with HTML like template syntax.
This makes the HTML file really easy to understand. This file makes applications robust and boosts its performance. 


 Why can’t browsers read JSX?
Browsers can only read JavaScript objects but 
JSX in not a regular JavaScript object. Thus to
 enable a browser to read JSX, first, we need to
  transform JSX file into a JavaScript object using
   JSX transformers like Babel and then pass it to the browser.



What is Props?
 They are always passed down from the parent to the child components


 a state in React



